cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the analysis of networks and their structure, which is a common topic in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on the intrinsic scale of networks and the use of random walks to study subgraphs suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The study of different types of networks, including biological networks, also suggests cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as possible sub-categories. The use of statistical methods and the analysis of network fragility and robustness suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as additional possibilities.
